{
  "texts": [
    "As shown in Table III, f d from the last layer achieves the best performance.",
    "Selection of Contrastive Loss.",
    "As shown in the lower half of Figure 1, we employ a contrastive loss between video feature and I-frame feature.",
    "The widely used InfoNCE loss [117] compares the feature with limited positive samples and multiple negative samples, which can be formalized as:L context = - 1 B B i=1 log exp( cos(z * i,xi) τ) exp( cos(z * i,xi) τ) + B k̸ =i exp( cos(z * k,xi) τ)(10)where x i denotes the global video representation, and z * i and z * k denote the positive and negative I-frame features, other symbols are the same as Equation 2.",
    "However, there may exist multiple I-frames in a single video clip, indicating more positive samples."
  ]
}